        <div class="teaser-listing-item">




<article class="teaser teaser-lg blog-entry--teaser" data-nid="5019514">

  <div class="teaser-lg--main">

          <div class="teaser-lg__image">
        
              <a href="/us/blog/canine-corner/202404/spayed-and-neutered-dogs-show-more-signs-of-aging"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_288x288/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-04/pexels-mikhail-nilov-7474855.jpg?h=1e2991c0&amp;itok=9XWPLpcq" width="288" height="288" alt="" title="Mikhail Nilov / Pexels" />

</a>

      
      </div>
    
    <div class="teaser-lg__details">
      
                        <div class="h2 teaser-lg__title">
            <a href="/us/blog/canine-corner/202404/spayed-and-neutered-dogs-show-more-signs-of-aging" rel="bookmark">Spayed and Neutered Dogs Show More Signs of Aging</a>
          </div>
              
      
              <p class="teaser-lg__summary teaser-lg__teaser--desktop">
            Spaying and neutering dogs is not an effective means of behavioral control but exposes dogs to severe physiological risks and increased signs of aging.
      </p>
          </div>

  </div>

      <p class="teaser-lg__summary teaser-lg__teaser--mobile">
            Spaying and neutering dogs is not an effective means of behavioral control but exposes dogs to severe physiological risks and increased signs of aging.
      </p>
  </article>
